## 3️⃣ Auto Refresh Token (IMPORTANT)

### Axios Interceptor (Recommended)

```js
axios.interceptors.response.use(
  res => res,
  async error => {
    if (error.response.status === 401) {
      const res = await axios.post("/refresh", {}, { withCredentials: true });
      setAccessToken(res.data.accessToken);
      error.config.headers.Authorization =
        `Bearer ${res.data.accessToken}`;
      return axios(error.config);
    }
    return Promise.reject(error);
  }
);
```

✅ User never sees login screen  
✅ Auto retry original request

***

## 4️⃣ On App Load (New Tab / Refresh)

```js
useEffect(() => {
  axios.post("/refresh", {}, { withCredentials: true })
    .then(res => setAccessToken(res.data.accessToken))
    .catch(() => console.log("Not logged in"));
}, []);
```

✅ This is what keeps the user logged in after opening a **new tab**

